---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Learn" description="Plain-English guides to how U.S. government works, what's on your ballot, and why it matters.">

  <!-- HERO: PAGE HEADER + RIGHT NOW -->
  <section class="bg-slate-900 text-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 pt-16 pb-12">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Learn</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-white/50 max-w-2xl mb-10">
        Plain-English guides to how U.S. government works, what's on your ballot, and why it matters. No spin&mdash;just the facts.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold tracking-wide uppercase text-white/40 mb-1">Right Now</h2>
      <div class="h-0.5 w-12 bg-tossup mb-6"></div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <a href="/learn/follow-the-money" class="group block bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6 hover:bg-white/10 transition-all">
          <span class="inline-block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-ind bg-ind/15 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full mb-4">
            Investigation
          </span>
          <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-3 group-hover:text-tossup transition-colors">
            Follow the Money
          </h3>
          <p class="text-white/60 leading-relaxed mb-4 text-sm">
            How DOGE, the crypto industry, and a $10 billion peace deal trace back to the 2024 election.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
            <span class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-navy/40 text-white/70">DOGE</span>
            <span class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-tossup/30 text-tossup">Crypto</span>
            <span class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-ind/30 text-ind">Board of Peace</span>
          </div>
          <span class="text-sm text-tossup font-medium group-hover:underline">
            Read the full timeline &rarr;
          </span>
        </a>

        <a href="/learn/save-act" class="group block bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6 hover:bg-white/10 transition-all">
          <span class="inline-block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-tossup bg-tossup/15 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full mb-4">
            Legislation
          </span>
          <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-3 group-hover:text-tossup transition-colors">
            The SAVE Act, Explained
          </h3>
          <p class="text-white/60 leading-relaxed mb-4 text-sm">
            What the SAVE America Act would change about voter registration and ID requirements&mdash;and what it means for the 2026 midterms.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-3 mb-4">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-white/40 mb-1">Current Status</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-white/80 leading-relaxed">
              <span class="font-semibold text-tossup">Passed House</span> 218&ndash;213<br/>
              Senate vote expected week of Feb 24
            </p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-sm text-tossup font-medium group-hover:underline">
            Read the full explainer &rarr;
          </span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE BODIES -->
  <section class="bg-slate-50 py-10 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold tracking-wide uppercase text-navy mb-1">The Bodies</h2>
      <div class="h-0.5 w-12 bg-navy mb-5"></div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <a href="/senate" class="group flex items-center gap-4 bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 hover:border-navy/40 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-navy/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
            <span class="text-navy font-bold text-sm">S</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-navy group-hover:text-dem transition-colors">The Senate</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">100 members &middot; 6-year terms</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/house" class="group flex items-center gap-4 bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 hover:border-navy/40 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-navy/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
            <span class="text-navy font-bold text-sm">H</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-navy group-hover:text-dem transition-colors">The House</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">435 members &middot; 2-year terms</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/governors" class="group flex items-center gap-4 bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 hover:border-navy/40 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-navy/10 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
            <span class="text-navy font-bold text-sm">G</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-navy group-hover:text-dem transition-colors">Governors</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">State executives &middot; 36 races in 2026</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- YOUR LEARNING PATH -->
  <section class="py-12 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-2">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-bold tracking-wide uppercase text-navy">Your Learning Path</h2>
        <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">16 guides &middot; 4 tracks</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-8 max-w-2xl">Start from the top and work your way down. Each guide builds on the last&mdash;by the end, you'll understand how money, power, and your vote connect.</p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

        <!-- TRACK 1: How Government Works -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-dem p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
              <span class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-dem/10 text-dem">Track 1</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">Guides 1&ndash;5</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-navy mb-3">How Government Works</h3>
            <ol class="space-y-3">
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/what-are-midterms" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-dem/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">01</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-dem transition-colors">What Are Midterm Elections?</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">What they are, why they matter, and what's on the ballot.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/how-congress-works" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-dem/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">02</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-dem transition-colors">How Congress Works</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">The Senate, the House, and how a bill becomes a law.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/bills-and-votes" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-dem/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">03</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-dem transition-colors">How Bills &amp; Votes Work</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">From introduction to the president's desk, plus filibusters and cloture.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/congressional-hearings" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-dem/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">04</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-dem transition-colors">Congressional Hearings</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">What they are, how they work, and whether they lead to anything.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/executive-orders" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-dem/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">05</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-dem transition-colors">Executive Orders</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">What they are, how they compare to laws, and what Congress can do.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- TRACK 2: Money & Power -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-tossup p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
              <span class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-tossup/10 text-tossup">Track 2</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">Guides 6&ndash;9</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-navy mb-3">Money &amp; Power</h3>
            <ol class="space-y-3">
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/career-ladder" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-tossup/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">06</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-tossup transition-colors">The Political Career Ladder</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">How politicians move between the House, Senate, and governor's mansion.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/how-to-run" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-tossup/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">07</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-tossup transition-colors">How to Run for Congress</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">Eligibility, filing, primaries, fundraising, and getting on the ballot.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/pacs-and-super-pacs" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-tossup/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">08</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-tossup transition-colors">PACs &amp; Super PACs</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">Where the money comes from, where it goes, and why it matters.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/follow-the-money" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-tossup/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">09</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-tossup transition-colors font-semibold">Follow the Money &#9733;</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">How DOGE, crypto, and a $10B peace deal trace back to the 2024 election.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- TRACK 3: Elections & Voting -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-navy p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
              <span class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-navy/10 text-navy">Track 3</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">Guides 10&ndash;13</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-navy mb-3">Elections &amp; Voting</h3>
            <ol class="space-y-3">
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/open-closed-primaries" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-navy/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">10</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-navy transition-colors">Open vs. Closed Primaries</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">How your party registration affects whether you can vote in a primary.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/race-ratings" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-navy/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">11</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-navy transition-colors">Understanding Race Ratings</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">What Safe, Likely, Lean, and Toss-Up mean and who decides.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/special-elections" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-navy/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">12</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-navy transition-colors">Special Elections</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">The elections nobody tells you about&mdash;and why so few voters decide them.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/voter-turnout" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-navy/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">13</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-navy transition-colors">Voter Turnout in America</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">How many Americans actually vote, who shows up, and why it matters.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- TRACK 4: Your Ballot -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-gop p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
              <span class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-gop/10 text-gop">Track 4</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">Guides 14&ndash;16</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-navy mb-3">Your Ballot</h3>
            <ol class="space-y-3">
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/reading-your-ballot" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-gop/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">14</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-gop transition-colors">Reading Your Ballot</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">A visual walkthrough of what you'll see when you vote.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/save-act" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-gop/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">15</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-gop transition-colors">The SAVE Act, Explained</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">What this bill would change about voter registration and ID requirements.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/learn/after-you-vote" class="group flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs font-mono text-gop/60 shrink-0 mt-0.5">16</span>
                  <div>
                    <span class="text-sm text-slate-700 group-hover:text-gop transition-colors">After You Vote</span>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-0.5">Ballot tracking, counting, certification, recounts, and runoffs.</p>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GO DEEPER -->
  <section class="bg-slate-900 py-12 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold tracking-wide uppercase text-white/40 mb-1">Go Deeper</h2>
      <div class="h-0.5 w-12 bg-tossup mb-6"></div>

      <a href="/deep-dives" class="group block bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 hover:bg-white/10 transition-all">
        <div class="md:flex md:items-start md:gap-8">
          <div class="flex-1">
            <span class="inline-block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-tossup bg-tossup/15 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full mb-4">
              3-Part Series
            </span>
            <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3 group-hover:text-tossup transition-colors">
              Presidential Overreach: The Pattern
            </h3>
            <p class="text-white/60 leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
              Every time a president breaks something, America tries to build a guardrail. For 230 years, the cycle has repeated. What do we build next?
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mb-4">
              <span class="text-xs text-white/50">&#x1F578; The Worst of All of Them</span>
              <span class="text-white/20">&middot;</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-white/50">&#x1F4CB; The Scorecard</span>
              <span class="text-white/20">&middot;</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-white/50">&#x1F9F9; Sweeping Up the Rubble</span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-sm text-tossup font-medium group-hover:underline">
              Read the series &rarr;
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GET INVOLVED -->
  <section class="bg-slate-50 py-12 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold tracking-wide uppercase text-navy mb-1">Get Involved</h2>
      <div class="h-0.5 w-12 bg-tossup mb-6"></div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/learn/how-to-run" class="group block bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 hover:border-navy/40 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-navy group-hover:text-dem transition-colors mb-2">How to Run for Congress</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Eligibility, filing, primaries, fundraising, and getting on the ballot.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/take-action" class="group block bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 hover:border-navy/40 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-navy group-hover:text-dem transition-colors mb-2">Take Action</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Register to vote, find your reps, and get involved in your community.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
